tinyproxy
------------------------------------------
Tinyproxy is a small, efficient HTTP/SSL proxy daemon released under the GNU
General Public License. Tinyproxy is very useful in a small network setting,
where a larger proxy would either be too resource intensive, or a security
risk. One of the key features of Tinyproxy is the buffering connection concept.
In effect, Tinyproxy will buffer a high speed response from a server, and then
relay it to a client at the highest speed the client will accept. This feature
greatly reduces the problems with sluggishness on the Internet. If you are
sharing an Internet connection with a small network, and you only want to allow
HTTP requests to be allowed, then Tinyproxy is a great tool for the network
administrator.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/tinyproxy/tinyproxy

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/tinyproxy/tinyproxy/archive/1.10.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack tinyproxy-1.10.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./tinyproxy-1.10.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/tinyproxy-1.10.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/tinyproxy-1.10.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(tinyproxy)
  /etc/tinyproxy/tinyproxy.conf
